definitions.definition: The Greek goddess of the hunt, wild animals , and wilderness ; the daughter of Leto and Zeus ; the sister of Apollo . ( Compare Diana . )
A female given name from Ancient Greek, masculine equivalent Artemios .
A male given name from Ancient Greek .
The main-belt asteroid 105 Artemis , discovered in 1868.
A United States space program , and the associated vehicles, used for human travel to the moon in the 2020s.
